  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>In simplest terms, an Item Type is a classification of items in your store to help organize your catalog. This allows you to assign specific attributes to the entire group of catalog items under these types. Item Types dictate price override allowances, identify whether items are parts or labor, establish parent/child relationships for bundling, and more.</p><p>Some reports are organized by item types, so you should create one item type for each category of revenue you want to analyze separately. By default, there are a variety of item types created for use but you can also create new item types and set their characteristics upon creation.</p><h3 id=\"CreatingaNewItemType-AdditionalResources\">Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427325\" rel=\"nofollow\">Catalog Settings Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931018355\" rel=\"nofollow\">Catalog Overview</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932329061\" rel=\"nofollow\">Creating a Catalog Item</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"680\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Instructional%20-%200091cd.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"CreatingaNewItemType-AddingaNewItemType\">Adding a New Item Type</h2><p>On the Navigation bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Company Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview screen, scroll down to the <strong>Catalog</strong> section and click <strong>Item Types</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Item%20Types%204.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"550\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Item%20Types%205.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Item Type page, click the <strong>Add Item Type</strong> button in the top-right corner of the page. Enter all applicable details and attributes for your Item Type. At a minimum, only the Name field is required. Adding supporting attributes will better help with the behaviors and classification of your type. Once you are finished making your selections, click the <strong>Save</strong> button to submit your changes.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: For an in-depth explanation of Item Type attributes, check out our article, <a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932427325\" rel=\"nofollow\">Catalog Settings Overview</a>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Item%20Types%201.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Item%20Types%202.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>After creating the new Item Type, it will appear on the overview page. From this screen, you can edit existing types or delete unused types.</p><p><strong>Note</strong>: You can only delete Item Types that do not have associated catalog items. This is to retain historical data and ensure proper record-keeping for data integrity.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932329027/Item%20Types%203.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
